<subSubSection id="E96D83ABC528423E498E8DAC5B59582F" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="BDA8C814680B5A0EFCEB28A7DF26B40A" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="927A543110E898CD2E1B10D6AC8E530D" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="9AC2097610401464783EB18156FE3E87" authorityName="Bordera &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Piasites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Piasites lineatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineatus">
<emphasis id="13F1FE0DFB13E142E6F30258485D1258" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Piasites lineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="0744C7DEBF51171DA6B96E31A674EF34" authorityName="Seyrig" authorityYear="1952" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Piasites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Piasites" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56E9AC535A80797EEB8D94D864D50625" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Piasites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the combination of the following characters: mesoscutum evenly convex, with moderately dense punctures on a shallow granulate background (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="255D66208414FD39F5D7A001A165C45B" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Piasites lineatus sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) D head and mesoscutum, dorsal view (holotype) E metasoma, dorsal view, arrow shows yellow cream dorsal stripe on hind coxa (paratype) F front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A, E); 0.5 mm (C); 0.3 mm (B, D, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677623" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">5C, D</figureCitation>
); mesopleuron densely and finely strigose punctate in dorsal part, ventrally finely and densely rugose punctate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="49306BCDA4CF61B58A833C68C182A40B" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Piasites lineatus sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) D head and mesoscutum, dorsal view (holotype) E metasoma, dorsal view, arrow shows yellow cream dorsal stripe on hind coxa (paratype) F front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A, E); 0.5 mm (C); 0.3 mm (B, D, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677623" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">5C</figureCitation>
); metapleuron transversely rugulose (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5A95BEC8A1CF2A780B8FD03891524326" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Piasites lineatus sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) D head and mesoscutum, dorsal view (holotype) E metasoma, dorsal view, arrow shows yellow cream dorsal stripe on hind coxa (paratype) F front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A, E); 0.5 mm (C); 0.3 mm (B, D, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677623" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">5C</figureCitation>
); juxtacoxal carina strong and complete (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="05E0B7D35DC42C8C910B678290540EEF" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Piasites lineatus sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) D head and mesoscutum, dorsal view (holotype) E metasoma, dorsal view, arrow shows yellow cream dorsal stripe on hind coxa (paratype) F front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A, E); 0.5 mm (C); 0.3 mm (B, D, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677623" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">5C</figureCitation>
); propodeum strongly and coarsely rugose (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B2152CFA62B03A0822B8C1609C6C37E1" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Propodeum of Piasites, dorsal view, females (II): A P. nigricollis sp. nov. (holotype) B P. orbitalis sp. nov. (holotype) C P. lineatus sp. nov. (paratype) D P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677619" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">2C</figureCitation>
); hind coxa black and yellow cream with a fine longitudinal yellow cream stripe at base (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="74AF7E16357F3C1FEBB2C991B301528C" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Piasites lineatus sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) D head and mesoscutum, dorsal view (holotype) E metasoma, dorsal view, arrow shows yellow cream dorsal stripe on hind coxa (paratype) F front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A, E); 0.5 mm (C); 0.3 mm (B, D, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677623" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">5E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="09DCB2F18F685CD532FC0A00DAA17CD4" doi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677623" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
